      "relations": null,
      "text": [
        " التَّقِيَّةُ فِي كُلِّ ضَرُورَةٍ وَ صَاحِبُهَا أَعْلَمُ بِهَا حِينَ تَنْزِلُ بِهِ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Ali Bin Ibrahim, from his father, from Hammad, from Rabi’e, from Zurara, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Ja’far<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘The dissimulation (<span class=\"iTxt\">Taqiyya</span>) (is to be done) during every necessity, and its performer is more knowing with it where he should be indulging in it’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "13. Ali ibn Ibrahim has narrated from his father from Hammad from Rib’i from Zurara from abu Ja’far (a.s.) who has said the following: “ Al-Taqiyyah (protective measures) is for when and wherever needed and the one involved in it knows best how to apply it.” "
        ]
      }
    }
